  "raw_response": "{\n  \"title\": \"EURUSD 5-min long setup using order block, gap below, and liquidity sweep\",\n  \"school\": \"Smart Money Concepts (SMC)\",\n  \"asset\": \"EURUSD\",\n  \"timeframe\": \"5-min\",\n  \"market_context\": \"Uptrend on EURUSD 5-min chart; price had formed a valid bearish order block followed by a gap below it and a second order block zone underneath. Analyst identified this as a high-probability long setup after liquidity sweep.\",\n  \"key_observation\": \"A valid order block was present, with a gap directly below it and a second order block beneath that; price was expected to fill the gap, sweep liquidity below the first OB, then continue upward after mitigating the second OB.\",\n  \"analysis_steps\": [\n    \"Step 1: The analyst identified a valid bearish order block (OB) on the EURUSD 5-min chart between ~14:30–15:30 at price 1.07105–1.07125.\",\n    \"Step 2: The analyst observed a gap (price inefficiency) located precisely below the first order block.\",\n    \"Step 3: The analyst noted a second valid order block zone positioned below the gap, forming a stacked structure.\",\n    \"Step 4: The analyst concluded that price would likely fill the gap, sweep liquidity below the first OB, and then continue upward after mitigating the second OB—thus not a valid CHoCH.\",\n    \"Step 5: The analyst emphasized entering only after stop-losses are swept, aligning with smart money behavior.\"\n  ],\n  \"outcome\": null,\n  \"lessons\": \"When a gap lies directly below a valid order block and another OB is stacked beneath",
